               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129649">
                  <summary>1 copy of Khizānat al-farāʻid al-Jalālīyah by Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn Aḥmad al-Bukhārī</summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_998-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Khizānat al-farāʻid al-Jalālīyah (جلال الدین حسین ابن احمد البخاری, discourses on Islamic theology and law by Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn Aḥmad ibn Ḥusayn al-Ḥusaynī al-Bukhārī (d.785/1385), as recorded by his disciple 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7787" role="aut">Bahāʼ al-Dīn Aḥmad ibn Yaʻqūb ibn Ḥusayn</persName>. The first discourse was completed on 5 Rabiʻ II 752 (1351).
                        </p>
                        <p>On f. 86v, there begins an account of the benefits of pilgrimages with a diagram (f. 88v) containing measurements of the places of pilgrimage at Mecca.</p>
                        <p>An added note claims that the work was copied for the Emperor Aurangzeb.</p>
                        <p>21 lines per page; nastaʻlīq; copyist, 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8003" role="scr">Ḥasan ibn Sulayman ibn ʻUsmān</persName>at Gujarat; rubrications; diagram on f. 88v  
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated 5 Zū al-Ḥijjah 1055 (22 Jan 1646).</p>
                        <p>See IO Islamic 577 (Ethe 2561) for another copy.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f1684">Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn Aḥmad al-Bukhārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f1684">جلال الدین حسین ابن احمد البخاری</persName>
                     </author>
